        <h1>Secret Societies & Esoteric Orders</h1>
        <p>Throughout history, certain groups have guarded esoteric knowledge, operating in secrecy to preserve traditions that challenge conventional understanding of reality, power, and human potential.</p>
        
        <div class="society-list">
            <div class="society-item">
                <div class="society-bg" style="background-image: url('https://i.etsystatic.com/23816357/r/il/2d72a3/3031197957/il_570xN.3031197957_1wr5.jpg')"></div>
                <div class="society-content">
                    <h3>The Rosicrucians</h3>
                    <p>A legendary esoteric order dating back to the early 17th century, combining elements of Hermeticism, Qabalah, and alchemy. Their manifestos promised a reformation of science, philosophy, and spirituality.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="society-item">
                <div class="society-bg" style="background-image: url('https://i1.sndcdn.com/artworks-000130177043-9zs2wd-t500x500.jpg')"></div>
                <div class="society-content">
                    <h3>Hermetic Order of the Golden Dawn</h3>
                    <p>A 19th-century British organization dedicated to the study and practice of the occult, metaphysics, and paranormal activities. It significantly influenced modern Western esotericism.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="society-item">
                <div class="society-bg" style="background-image: url('https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/480xn/p05byvkr.jpg.webp')"></div>
                <div class="society-content">
                    <h3>The Illuminati</h3>
                    <p>Founded in 1776, this Enlightenment-era secret society sought to oppose religious influence over public life and abuse of state power. It has since become the subject of numerous conspiracy theories.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="society-item">
                <div class="society-bg" style="background-image: url('https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:699/1*XjAgTFN_10GJL1H1faxKSg.jpeg')"></div>
                <div class="society-content">
                    <h3>The Knights Templar</h3>
                    <p>A Catholic military order founded in 1119, rumored to have discovered esoteric knowledge during their time in Jerusalem, possibly including the Holy Grail or Ark of the Covenant.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="society-item">
                <div class="society-bg" style="background-image: url('https://www.deathcampsmemorialsite.com/images/wpisy/022020/thule2.jpg')"></div>
                <div class="society-content">
                    <h3>The Thule Society</h3>
                    <p>A German occultist and völkisch group in Munich, named after a mythical northern country from Greek legend. It developed into the German Workers' Party, which transformed into the Nazi Party.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
